FG-211 — One-Pager to Chambers (Facts • Pins • Ask)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: A crisp chambers letter = facts + two pins + one signable ask.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ≤120 words; neutral tone; cite local policy if required; attach exhibit only if invited; mirror the ask in a proposed order.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line chambers letter with two pins and a 1-line order.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Issue: harm not reached (Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2). Relief: limited remand 21d for findings (a–d).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Less emotion, more pins.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A short letter clipped to a tiny order card.

⸻

FG-212 — “One Tab, One Purpose” (Kill the Dump)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Every appendix tab exists to prove one thing.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Label each tab with its purpose; remove duplicates; add a 1-line purpose note at tab start; crosswalk to the brief.
	•	📝 Assignment: Rewrite five tab labels to purpose form.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Tab 3 — ‘Harm not reached’ support (Dkt 18:2).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Purpose beats piles.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Tabs with short purpose labels, color-coded.

⸻

FG-213 — Posture Footers on Every Draft (Triangle in Miniature)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Stamp statute • clock • copies at the page bottom.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Small footer: “§1291; Rule 58 08/15; NOA 08/19; Tabs 1–2”; remove if final uses first-paragraph posture.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add a 1-line posture footer to your working draft.
	•	✅ Model Response: “§1291; Rule 58 08/15; NOA 08/19; Tabs 1–2.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Comfort travels with the page.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slim footer triangle icon with three labels.

⸻

FG-214 — OA Time Captain (Clock • Reserve • Signals)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: One teammate owns the clock and the reserve.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Captain cues reserve :60, tracks signal topics (ticks per judge), and flashes the close when signals align.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write a 4-line captain checklist for your next OA.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Reserve :60; track harm Qs; cue two-pin close at 1:00.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Time discipline = argument discipline.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small headset icon over a ticking clock.

⸻

FG-215 — Cite-Ready Exhibits (Auth Page First)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Cite auth page before content so no one hunts.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: For each exhibit: Auth (Decl ¶ / stamp / EXIF) → Content → Factor; duplicate the auth page into the tab front if needed.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add auth-first cites for two exhibits in your brief.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Auth: Decl ¶4 (Tab S-1 p.1) → Content: invoice (Tab 3 p.2) → Factor: harm cost.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Provenance precedes persuasion.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A lock icon pinned before a content page.

⸻

FG-216 — Micro-Calendar Reset (Two Dates, One Line)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Ask for two dates in one sentence with the math shown elsewhere.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: “Reply due [date]; OA window [two slots]”; support with a clock table in a short notice.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a one-line reset and a 4-row clock table.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Reply 09/22; OA Tue/Wed 2–4 PM; Rule 58 08/15 → +30 → 09/14 → weekend → 09/15.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Dates sign faster than paragraphs.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two calendar tiles with a slim math box.

⸻

FG-217 — Protective Language for Settlement (No Admissions • Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Convert terms into consent language with protection.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Recitals neutral; no admissions; hash any attached public docs; add retained jurisdiction (short window) for enforcement.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft three protective lines for a consent judgment.
	•	✅ Model Response: “No admission of liability; public attachments hashed; retained jurisdiction 60 days.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Safety text makes peace hold.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A handshake over a small “consent” stamp and hash tag.

⸻

FG-218 — Transcript-Substitute Discipline (FRAP 10(c) One-Pager)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: A 10(c) statement must be neutral, pinned, and short.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Heading; bullet timeline; neutral descriptions; pins to notes/emails; proposed adoption line; lodge for settlement.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 1-page 10(c) skeleton with 6 bullets and two pins.
	•	✅ Model Response: “On 08/02 court stated it would not reach harm (notes; email Ex A).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Accuracy earns adoption.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A transcript silhouette replaced by a clean one-pager.

⸻

FG-219 — Mediation-Ready Consent (Order Text First)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Bring order words to the mediation, not just positions.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Pre-draft consent judgment outline (relief/scope/dates/reporting); convert the deal into a tick-box order on the spot.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write a three-paragraph consent outline with dates.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Deliver relief in 30/60/90; status 30d; retained jurisdiction 90d; costs by stip.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Deals that draft themselves stick.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A draft order with checkboxes sliding under two signatures.

⸻

FG-220 — “One Screen” Exhibit Index (OA & Appendix)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put every exhibit on one screen with pins and purpose.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Ex • Purpose • Auth pin • Content pin • Factor; hash at footer; mirror in appendix and OA index.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build an exhibit index card (≤20 rows) and add to packet front.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Ex A — USPS receipt — Auth Decl ¶4 (S-1 p.1) — Content Tab 3 p.2 — Factor: harm.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One card makes “where?” disappear.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A compact grid with five columns and a fingerprint footer.